&lt;h1 id="does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths"&gt;Does one have to be a genius to do maths?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Better beware of notions like genius and inspiration; they are a sort of magic wand and should be used sparingly by anybody who wants to see things clearly.
(José Ortega y Gasset, &amp;ldquo;Notes on the novel&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Does one have to be a genius to do mathematics?&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Solving mathematical problems</title><link>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/orig/solving-mathematical-problems/</link><pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2007 00:44:38 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/orig/solving-mathematical-problems/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/zh/solving-mathematical-problems.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
