 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id="work-hard"&gt;Work hard&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Every mathematician worthy of the name has experienced … the state of lucid exaltation in which one thought succeeds another as if miraculously… this feeling may last for hours at a time, even for days. Once you have experienced it, you are eager to repeat it but unable to do it at will, unless perhaps by dogged work…&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Weil"&gt;André Weil&lt;/a&gt;, “The Apprenticeship of a Mathematician”)&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How to Work Hard</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/hwh/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/hwh/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/hwh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
